git revert 

   git revert safely undoes a commit by creating a new commit, making it the preferred rollback mechanism for production, CI/CD, and team-based workflows

-----------


FILE GOT DELETED , How to restore ?

if it is in workspace : git restore fname

if it is in Staging : 
   git restore --staged filename
   git restore filename


File was deleted AND committed 

   git log -- filename
   git checkout <commit-hash> -- filename
   git commit -m "Restore filename"

===================================================================
git clean :

- it clean deletes untracked files (and with -d, untracked directories).
- It does not affect tracked files or commit history.- 

